analysis: The agent formatted the "trends" values for the fashion_week_trend_analyzer function incorrectly, using "elegant designs" and "vibrant colors" instead of the required normalized "elegant" and "vibrant," causing a parameter mismatch with the expected function call schema.
The agent only called CommodityDataRetriever_fetchCommodityInfo and failed to call finance_credit_scoring for the credit score analysis, thus neglecting a key part of the user's request.

The agent incorrectly set the "complexity" field for the "writingPrompt" tool to "detailed" instead of the required "advanced," failing to match the expected function call parameters exactly for CreativeSession_startWritingSession.

The agent omitted the "healthIssues" field for the first employee (should be an empty list), causing its function call arguments to mismatch the expected schema even though all substance was present. This led to evaluation failure.

The agent used "comprehensive" instead of the required "detailed" for the "analysisDepth" parameter in the CinemaPhilosophyAnalyzer_analyzeSocietalThemes function call, causing a mismatch with the expected function call signature.

The agent incorrectly placed the "time" parameter at the top level of the function call instead of nesting it inside the "customer" object as required by the expected parameters schema, resulting in a mismatch.

The agent paraphrased the document content as "Content on fundamental physics concepts" instead of the expected "Fundamental physics concepts," leading to an argument mismatch and failing to match the required function call signature for document_management_store.

The agent output multiple tool calls in a single response but wrapped each in separate <tool_call> tags with JSON, likely violating the expected output format and causing parsing errors due to extra closing braces or trailing characters after the first JSON object.

The agent only verified the originality of the first content item instead of processing all five provided by the user, failing to issue function calls for the remaining four contents as required by the task.

The agent only made a single function call instead of the required four, failing to cover all requested time periods and regions. It also included an unnecessary "interactions" detail and omitted separate calls for each time/location as specified in the request.

The agent assigned the wrong severity value (4 instead of 3) for the "swelling" symptom in the ReptileBiteResponseSystem_evaluateBiteSeverity function call, causing its function arguments to not match the expected parameters and resulting in no match.

The agent omitted the "themes" parameter with the value "Existentialism" in the PhilosophyCinemaExplorer_findPurposeDrivenFilms function call, resulting in an incomplete and unmatched function invocation per the expected tool signature.

The agent incorrectly added an unsupported "advisoryDetails" parameter to the CityTravelAdvisor_getTravelAdvisories function call, causing a mismatch with the expected API signature and resulting in evaluator rejection.
The agent omitted the required "event_details" parameter in its function calls, resulting in a mismatch with the expected format and causing the evaluator to not recognize its output as valid.

The agent only analyzed the pond sample instead of making separate contaminant detection calls for each of the five provided water sources, failing to process all requested samples as specified in the user's instructions.

The agent failed to include the required "infrastructureResponse" parameter in each SmartTrafficSystem_manageV2ICommunication function call and omitted the "Car" prefix in vehicleID, resulting in incorrect and incomplete function arguments.

The agent only made a single function call using the first user's profile, instead of generating separate finance_recommendation_system calls for each profile as requested. It failed to process all five profiles individually.

The agent omitted the required "date": "Immediate" parameter in the RealEstateAdvisor_getMortgageDetails function call, resulting in a mismatch with the expected function call signature and thus evaluation failure.

The agent failed to represent the parallel connection between the two resistors in the second circuit, using a vague "from": "resistor", "to": "resistor" connection instead of correctly distinguishing and labeling the resistors as separate entities ("resistor1", "resistor2") and indicating a parallel arrangement.

The agent only submitted a function call for planning the Music Festival, completely omitting the required call for the Art Exhibition, thus failing to address both user-specified events as requested.

The agent omitted the "other_elements": [] field in the "initial_composition" parameter for both function calls, resulting in function call argument mismatches and failure to match the expected function signature.

The agent combined requests for history and literature into a single function call instead of making two separate calls—one for history timeline creation and one for deep literature text analysis—resulting in an incomplete and conflated response.

The agent added unnecessary "pollution_parameters" details to the ecosystem_impact_assessment function call, resulting in a parameter mismatch and failure to match the expected function signature. Only the required top-level parameters should have been supplied.

The agent incorrectly included an empty "contact_number" field within "applicant_details" for each function call, resulting in argument structures that did not match the expected parameters and causing the evaluator to reject the calls as mismatches.
The agent incorrectly set the assessmentDate to "2023-06" (this month) instead of "2022-06" (last month) as specified by the user's request, leading to function call argument mismatches.

The agent included extraneous <tool_call> XML tags around the JSON output, resulting in invalid JSON with trailing characters that caused parsing to fail. The tool call should be pure JSON without additional markup.

The agent incorrectly set the "reverb" effect's intensity to 0.9 instead of the expected maximum (1), included an unnecessary "apply_time" parameter, and used "arguments" instead of "parameters" in the function call, causing a mismatch with the expected signature.

The agent incorrectly included empty "secondary" keys in the "fonts" object and outputted tool calls with invalid formatting (extra braces, invalid tags), resulting in unparsable JSON and mismatch with the expected function call structure.

The agent failed to include the required "timeOfDay" parameter in both function calls, resulting in a mismatch with the function signatures and causing the evaluator to reject the output despite correct values for all other parameters.

The agent produced invalid JSON for the HomeLightingControl_manageLightSettings call by using an extra layer of array brackets for "settings" and mismatched curly braces, leading to a parsing failure and preventing execution.

The agent made typographical errors in the "scenario" fields ("vial" vs. "viral", "stiking" vs. "striking"), causing mismatches with the expected function call parameters and resulting in evaluation failure.

The agent included an extra closing curly brace at the end of the JSON for the CaseDocumentManager_uploadLegalDocument tool call, resulting in malformed JSON that caused parsing to fail. The error is due to incorrect JSON syntax, not logic.

The agent incorrectly combined both countries into a single function call and omitted the required "medal_types" parameter, instead of making separate calls for each country with all medal types specified.

The model used "EiffelTower" instead of the correct "Eiffel Tower" for the attractionId parameter, resulting in a function call argument mismatch with the expected call. This caused the evaluator to not find a matching function signature.

The agent incorrectly used "recent joyful mood" as the "moodDescription" argument instead of extracting just "joyful," leading to a mismatch with the expected function call parameters for MusicMoodAnalyzer_analyzeAndSuggestTracks.

The agent produced the correct function names and structure, but there was a typo in the emailContent field ("Exlusive" instead of "Exclusive") for the second campaign, causing the function call not to match the expected parameters exactly.
